A classical problem in risk theory - what is the ruin probability of an insurance company - is considered, using the model of collective risk. Then basic models of modern portfolio theory are covered, including Markowitz and capital asset pricing models (CAPM). VaR-methodology for measuring financial risks is introduced.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1. Overview of variety of risks in financial and insurance risks. 2.  To provide a mathematical basis for the study of risks (classical risk model) and various measures of risk.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Passing through the module, a participant 1. understands the concept of risk and differentiates various types of risk in financial industry; 2. knows classical results of ruin theory and is able to apply them in solving practical problems; 3. knows main principles of modern portfolio theory and the capital asset pricing model (CAPM); 4. knows principles of VaR measures and is able to perform necessary calculations.
